  institution = {Faculdade Cultura Inglesa},
  location = {São Paulo},
  abstract = {The example of good teachers in my life prompted me to study the meaning, the essence of good teaching practice. The means to conduct this study was found in an opportunity to teach the C1 Advanced Preparation Tutorial at Faculdade Cultura Inglesa in a remote learning setting over two terms in 2020 and two terms in 2021. Reflective tools were employed to observe and analyse the phenomena in the virtual classroom via reflection-in-action and reflection-on-action (SCHÖN, 1983) on an iterative basis to ensure a continuous process of improvement of my pedagogical practice (CELANI, 2008; KOLB, 2015; FREEMAN, 1998). Reflective practice procedures (SCHÖN, 1983; VAN MANEN, 2016) allowed for the identification of needs for adjustment in the first sessions of the tutorial that led to changes required to increase the relevance of the learning experience of the students. After reviewing the main results, this article will conclude by demonstrating the effectiveness of the reflective practice procedures (SCHÖN, 1983; VAN MANEN, 2016) in adapting classes to remote learning settings while establishing a safe learning environment, raising the teachers' awareness of the students' learning objectives and motivations while still maintaining a high-quality learning experience.},
